summary:
I am graduated Master of Philosophy in International Community Health. My research analyzed the oral health problems with irregular migrants in Oslo (Norway), their coping strategies. 
To overcome the risks of ignored dental care for vulnerable groups, access to care requires also a level of improved communication. 
I wish to apply my skills and knowledge in the projects aiming to improve health of population either at global or at local level. 
Most of my experiences related to human health I gained through diagnosis, treatment and prevention of oral health diseases. I have been practicing dentist for 6 years. During my work as dentist and second study on International Community Health, I grew a passion to work with people and to contribute to the improvement of their health.
